From cou.: 13 Adhesion lap shear tests were performed at room temperature using a method based on ASTM D3163, using the Instron 5544, see Fig. 1. When the adherents were completely separated, an abrupt drop in adhesion strength was observed. The maximum adhesion strength observed before the sudden drop in force was utilized for all reported adhesion strength measurements. The adherents utilized were made of PS or PI. All results are the average of eight or more samples being tested.
From Soup: 13 Adhesion lap shear tests were performed at room temperature using a method based on ASTM D3163, using the Instron 5544, see Fig. 1 . When the adherents were completely separated, an abrupt drop in adhesion strength was observed. The maximum adhesion strength observed before the sudden drop in force was utilized for all reported adhesion strength measurements. The adherents utilized were made of PS or PI. All results are the average of eight or more samples being tested.
