From cou.: 18 The orientation of the methyl groups on the epoxy can be deduced using SFG spectra collected using different polarization combinations of the input/output beams and the nonlinear susceptibility components of the vibrational modes. The two methyl groups on BADGE (Fig. 1) have been previously modeled as an isopropyl group, which means the entire (CH3)2C unit is treated as a single unit, rather than two methyl groups.67 The two methyl groups have a fixed angle 2α = 112° and it was assumed that the methyl groups can freely rotate, which means the (CH3)2C group has quasi-C2v symmetry. The results of the nonvanishing components of the second-order nonlinear susceptibility, χ(2), are:
